er nearly its entire sunward facing hemisphere in September and\nOctober but which underwent a significant mass loss event, potentially\nincluding fragmentation, shortly before November 1. Significant mass loss\nlikely continued at the same site over subsequent days/weeks and may have\ncatastrophically weakened the nucleus prior to perihelion.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 2 Oct 2014 20:00:06 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-23"}
